Here is an example of a simple Discord bot using Discord.js v14 with one command, `ban`. The bot will respond to messages started with `/ban <user>` where `<user>` is the username of the user to be banned. 

First, make sure to install the required packages:

```
npm install discord.js
```

Next, create a file `index.js` with the following content:

```javascript
const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');
const client = new Client({ intents: [Intents.FLAGS.GUILDS, Intents.FLAGS.GUILD_MESSAGES] });

client.once('ready', () => {
  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
});

client.on('messageCreate', message => {
  if (message.content === '/ban @user') {
    const user = message.guild.members.cache.get(message.cleanContent);
    if (user) {
      message.reply('Banning...');
      user.ban(reason => {
        message.reply(`Banned ${user. username}! Reason: ${reason}`);
      });
    } else {
      message.reply('User not found!');
    }
  }
});

client.login('your-bot-token');
```

Replace `'your-bot-token'` with your bot token from the Discord Developer Portal.

